    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Shillingford Rectory Exeter.</placeName>
                    <date>Oct. 10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1881.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir—</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Absence from home during two days has prevented from acknowledging before today, as I now do, the safe receipt of your Second Letter—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> And I beg to render you my sincere thanks for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. kindness in replying to my questions, by which I am enabled to understand, better than I did before, the hypothesis of the doctrine of Evolution.</p>
<p>I beg to remain, Dear Sir, | Yours faithfully | B. W. Savile <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">C. Darwin Esq</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            
            
        </div>
        
        
